        "Fact:- The heart of a shrimp is located in its head. This is just one of the many unusual biological features of these small marine creatures.",
        "Fact:- Flamingos are born with gray feathers and only turn pink because of the chemicals in the shrimp and algae they eat. Their color is a direct result of their diet.",
        "Fact:- Koalas have fingerprints that are almost identical to human fingerprints. They are so similar that they have sometimes been confused at crime scenes.",
        "Fact:- A group of owls is called a parliament. This name reflects the historical belief that owls are wise and dignified creatures.",
        "Fact:- Pigs are considered one of the most intelligent animals on the planet and can even learn to play video games. They have cognitive abilities that surpass those of many young children.",
