        "Fact:- A group of toads is called a knot. Toads are often found in gardens where they help control pest populations by eating insects.",
        "Fact:- Blue whales are the loudest animals on Earth and their songs can reach 188 decibels. These low-frequency sounds can travel across entire oceans.",
        "Fact:- A group of trout is called a hover. Trout are popular freshwater fish that are known for their beautiful patterns and strong swimming ability.",
        "Fact:- Woodpeckers have long, sticky tongues that they use to reach insects hidden deep inside tree trunks. Their tongues can be up to four inches long depending on the species.",
        "Fact:- A group of unicorns is called a blessing. While they are mythical creatures, this name reflects the positive and magical qualities often attributed to them.",
        "Fact:- Bees can see ultraviolet light which helps them find nectar in flowers that look plain to the human eye. Many flowers have 'bullseye' patterns that only bees can see.",
        "Fact:- A group of walruses is called a herd. Walruses use their sensitive whiskers to find shellfish on the dark ocean floor.",
        "Fact:- Cats can make over 100 different sounds whereas dogs can only make about ten. This variety of vocalizations helps cats communicate subtle needs to their owners.",
        "Fact:- A group of whales is called a pod. Whales are social animals that communicate through a series of complex clicks and whistles.",
        "Fact:- Male penguins carry the eggs on their feet to keep them warm during the harsh Antarctic winter. They huddle together with other males to share body heat until the eggs hatch.",
        "Fact:- A group of wombats is called a wisdom. Wombats are burrowing animals that are known for their sturdy build and unique cube-shaped droppings.",
        "Fact:- Ants can survive for up to twenty-four hours underwater by entering a state of suspended animation. They are incredibly resilient and can thrive in almost any environment.",
        "Fact:- A group of woodlucks is called a fall. Woodchucks are also known as groundhogs and are famous for their supposed ability to predict the arrival of spring.",
        "Fact:- Elephants have a highly developed sense of self-awareness and can recognize themselves in a mirror. This is a sign of high intelligence and complex emotional processing.",
        "Fact:- A group of yaks is called a herd. Yaks are large, long-haired mammals that live in the high altitudes of the Himalayas.",
        "Fact:- Sea turtles have been swimming in the oceans for over 100 million years. They have survived the extinction of the dinosaurs and continue to play a vital role in marine ecosystems.",
        "Fact:- A group of zebras is called a dazzle. This name comes from the way their stripes blend together when they move, making it hard for predators to target one individual.",
        "Fact:- Polar bear fur is not actually white but transparent and hollow. It reflects the light from the sun which makes the bears appear white to our eyes.",
        "Fact:- A group of alpacas is called a herd. Alpacas are prized for their soft and warm fleece which is used to make high-quality clothing.",
