        "Fact:- Butterflies can only see the colors red, green, and yellow. Despite this limited range, they are able to find flowers and mates with great accuracy.",
        "Fact:- A group of camels is called a caravan. Camels are perfectly adapted for life in the desert with their ability to go long periods without water.",
        "Fact:- Male seahorses can give birth to up to 2,000 babies at one time. They are dedicated fathers that provide a safe place for the eggs to develop.",
        "Fact:- A group of caterpillars is called an army. Caterpillars spend most of their lives eating so they can grow large enough to transform into butterflies.",
