        "Fact:- A group of cheetahs is called a coalition. Unlike other big cats, cheetahs are built for speed rather than power and can reach sixty miles per hour in seconds.",
        "Fact:- Squirrels will pretend to bury nuts to trick other animals that might be watching them. This clever behavior helps protect their real food supplies from being stolen.",
