        "Fact:- A cat's nose is as unique as a human's fingerprint. Each cat has a distinct pattern of ridges and bumps on their nose leather.",
        "Fact:- A group of crocodiles is called a float when they are in the water and a bask when they are on land. They are powerful predators that have existed for millions of years.",
        "Fact:- Hummingbirds are the only animals that can hover in place for long periods of time. They do this by flapping their wings in a figure-eight pattern.",
        "Fact:- A group of deer is called a herd. Deer are found on every continent except Antarctica and Australia, and are known for their grace and speed.",
