        "Fact:- A group of donkeys is called a drove. Donkeys are strong and dependable animals that have been used by humans for thousands of years.",
        "Fact:- Sea otters use their stomachs as a table to eat their food while floating on their backs. They are one of the few animals that use tools in their daily lives.",
        "Fact:- A group of eagles is called a convocation. Eagles are majestic birds of prey that are known for their incredible eyesight and powerful talons.",
